e and Azure architecture.\nReduced\ndata latency for store managers from 24 hours to 15 seconds. Internal Analytical Excellence: Developed the Sterling Analysis Framework, a standardized\nelicitation and documentation rubric adopted by 200 analysts organization-wide.\nReduced\nrequirement rework by 40 and accelerated development velocity by 25. Talent Acquisition  Mentorship: Established the Strategic Analyst Fellowship, an internal\nmentorship program that has successfully promoted 12 junior analysts to\nLeadPrincipal roles", "start_date": "2020-07-01", "end_date": null, "is_current": true}, {"job_title": "within 24 months. Senior Strategic Business Analyst  Vanguard Consulting Group", "company_name": "Charlotte, NC (Global Management  Technology Consultancy)", "description": "Operational Leadership: Served as the lead consultant for the Health-Nexus account, a con-\nsortium of Tier-1 healthcare providers. Directed a team of 30 analysts focused on\nMA technical\nintegration and regulatory compliance. Key Measurable Achievements: MA Technical Integration: Directed the business analysis for the 2.2B merger of two ma-\njor healthcare networks (fictional client: Carolina Health Group). Successfully integrated\n400 clinical systems and synchronized 12M patient records with zero data loss. HIPAA Compliance Automation: Architected an automated compliance auditing tool that\nanalyzed system logs against federal privacy standards. Reduced annual audit preparation\ntime by 1,200 man-hours and identified 15 high-risk data exposure points before exploitation. Telehealth Platform Rollout: Led the requirement gathering and vendor selection for a\nregion-wide telehealth platform during the COVID-19 pandemic. Achieved a rapid 60-day de-\nployment that served 500,000 patients in the first month. Operational Cost Reduction: Conducted a comprehensive Current State vs.\nFuture State\ngap analysis for the clinical procurement process. Identified 8M in redundant spend through\nvendor consolidation and automated PO approval workflows. UXUI Transformation: Partnered with UX researchers to redesign the clinician portal.\nUsed\ndata-driven analysis of click-paths to reduce documentation time for nurses by 15 minutes\nper shift. Executive Reporting: Built a real-time Transformation KPI dashboard in\nTableau for the\nclients Board of Directors. Provided visibility into project burn-rates, risk mitigation, and re-", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true}, {"job_title": "alized business value. Senior Business Systems Analyst  FinEdge Solutions", "company_name": "New York, NY (Financial Technology  Core Banking Infrastructure)", "description": "Role Overview: Primary analytical lead for the Global-Pay initiative, focusing on high-frequency\npayment processing and regulatory reporting. Key Measurable Achievements: Core Banking Migration: Managed the functional requirements for a legacy-to-modern core\nbanking transition for a top-tier institutional bank. Reduced system downtime during main-\ntenance windows by 80 through optimized batch processing logic. AMLKYC Process Re-engineering: Redesigned the Know Your Customer onboarding work-\nflow using BPMN 2.0. Automated 60 of the verification steps, reducing customer onboard-\ning time from 5 days to 4 hours. API Strategy Implementation: Authored the functional specifications for a suite of 200\npublic and private APIs, enabling the banks entry into the Open Banking ecosystem.\nDirectly\nsupported 50M in new partner-driven revenue. UAT Excellence: Directed the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for a new institutional trading\ndashboard. Managed 150 test users across 5 regions, achieving a Gold\nStatus release with\nzero post-launch critical bugs. Performance Optimization: Collaborated with database architects to optimize\nSQL query\nlogic for real-time risk reports. Reduced report generation time from 5 minutes to 12 seconds", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true}]}
