s (Data Generation), Polly (Resilience). Infrastructure, Cloud  DevOps\n Microsoft Azure Stack: Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), Azure App Service, Azure Functions (Server-\nless), Azure DevOps (YAML Pipelines), Bicep, Azure Front Door. DevOps  Automation: GitHub Actions, Jenkins (Groovy DSL), Azure Pipelines, Octopus Deploy, ArgoCD (GitOps), FluxCD. Containerization: Docker Desktop, Podman, Helm Charts, KEDA, Service Mesh (Linkerd, Istio, Cilium), Container Security (Trivy). IaC  Configuration: Terraform, ARM Templates, Pulumi, Ansible, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp\nVault. Database  Messaging Platforms\n Persistence: SQL Server 2022 (In-Memory OLTP, Temporal Tables), Azure SQL DB, Cosmos DB, PostgreSQL (PostGIS), MariaDB. Messaging: Azure Service Bus, Kafka (Confluent), RabbitMQ, NServiceBus, MassTransit (AzureRab-\nbitMQ Transports), SignalR Backplane. Cache  Search: Redis (Cluster, Redlock), Memcached, Elasticsearch 8.x, Meilisearch, Algolia, Vec-\ntor Databases (Pinecone). Architectural Standards  Monitoring\n Observability: Application Insights, Datadog (APM), Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry, Splunk, Loki, Jaeger (Distributed Tracing). Methodologies: Domain-Driven Design (DDD), SOLID, DRY, YAGNI, Lean Software Development, SAFE (Scaled Agile), AgileKanban. Design Documentation: SwaggerOpenAPI 3.1, Mermaid.js, Lucidchart (C4 Modeling), Conflu-\nence, Architecture Decision Records (ADR). PROFESSIONAL EXPERI", "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "SQL DB", "company_name": "SQL DB", "role": "", "job_title": "", "location": null, "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "bitMQ Transports", "clients": ["bitMQ Transports"], "description": "(150M), Global Team Scaling. Data Engineering: SQL Server Optimization (Performance Tuning, Sharding), PostgreSQL (Citus), MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis Caching, ElasticsearchELK. Messaging  Streaming: Apache Kafka, Azure Service Bus, RabbitMQ, MassTransit, NServiceBus, EventStoreDB, KEDA for autoscaling. Security  Compliance: OAuth2OpenID Connect, JWT, mTLS, OWASP Top 10 Mitigation, HIPAA, PCI-DSS, SOC2 Compliance, Zero-Trust Architecture. Quality  Testing: Test-Driven Development (TDD), Consumer-Driven Contract Testing (Pact), Chaos Engineering, Playwright Automation, BenchmarkDotNet. TECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nDevelopment Frameworks  Languages\n Languages: C (Expert), F (Functional Patterns), TypeScript, JavaScript, Go, SQL, PowerShell, Bash, Python, Rust (FFI Integration). Backend Frameworks:.NET 89, ASP.NET Core (Minimal APIs, SignalR), Entity Framework Core\n(Source Generators), Dapper, Akka.NET, Microsoft Orleans. Frontend Integration: Blazor (WASMServer), React 18 (Hooks, Suspense), Angular 17, Next.js\n(BFF Patterns), Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion. Architecture Tools: MediatR, FluentValidation, Serilog (Structured Logging), AutoFixture, Moq, xUnit, Bogus (Data Generation), Polly (Resilience). Infrastructure, Cloud  DevOps\n Microsoft Azure Stack: Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), Azure App Service, Azure Functions (Server-\nless), Azure DevOps (YAML Pipelines), Bicep, Azure Front Door. DevOps  Automation: GitHub Actions, Jenkins (Groovy DSL), Azure Pipelines, Octopus Deploy, ArgoCD (GitOps), FluxCD. Containerization: Docker Desktop, Podman, Helm Charts, KEDA, Service Mesh (Linkerd, Istio, Cilium), Container Security (Trivy). IaC  Configuration: Terraform, ARM Templates, Pulumi, Ansible, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp\nVault. Database  Messaging Platforms\n Persistence: SQL Server 2022 (In-Memory OLTP, Temporal Tables), Azure SQL DB, Cosmos DB, PostgreSQL (PostGIS), MariaDB. Messaging: Azure Service Bus, Kafka (Confluent), RabbitMQ, NServiceBus, MassTransit (AzureRab-\nbitMQ Transports), SignalR Backplane. Cache  Search: Redis (Cluster, Redlock), Memcached, Elasticsearch 8.x, Meilisearch, Algolia, Vec-\ntor Databases (Pinecone). Architectural Standards  Monitoring\n Observability: Application Insights, Datadog (APM), Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry, Splunk, Loki, Jaeger (Distributed Tracing). Methodologies: Domain-Driven Design (DDD), SOLID, DRY, YAGNI, Lean Software Development, SAFE (Scaled Agile), AgileKanban. Design Documentation: SwaggerOpenAPI 3.1, Mermaid.js, Lucidchart (C4 Modeling), Conflu-\nence, Architecture Decision Records (ADR). PROFESSIONAL EXPERI", "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "Nexus FinTech Systems", "company_name": "Nexus FinTech Systems", "role": "Global Director Of Engineering Principal.Net Architect", "job_title": "Global Director Of Engineering Principal.Net Architect", "location": null, "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "", "clients": [], "description": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "Core Ledger Payments division", "company_name": "Core Ledger Payments division", "role": "technical authority", "job_title": "technical authority", "location": "Austin, TX Remote", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "Digital Banking Infrastructure", "clients": ["Digital Banking Infrastructure"], "description": ": Enterprise.NET Transformation: Led the massive migration from a monolithic ASP.NET 4.8 frame-\nwork to a containerized.NET 8 microservices ecosystem on Azure. Achieved a 65 reduction in\ninfrastructure costs while increasing transaction throughput by 400. Global Payments Architecture: Architected a distributed, event-driven payment engine utiliz-\ning Azure Service Bus and MassTransit. Implemented the SAGA pattern for complex transaction\ncoordination, resulting in a 99.9 successful settlement rate across 22 currencies. Performance Engineering: Identified and remediated critical memory leaks in the.NET Garbage\nCollector for high-traffic services. Optimized Entity Framework Core queries using Compiled\nQueries and NoTracking, reducing SQL Server CPU utilization by 45 during peak hours. Identity  Security Modernization: Directed the deployment of a unified identity provider using\nIdentityServer6 and Azure AD B2C. Implemented multi-factor authentication (MFA) and biometric\nauth for 12M end-users, ensuring 100 compliance with PCI-DSS 4.0. Productivity Automation: Developed an internal Developer Portal using Backstage.io and C-\nbased scaffolding tools. Reduced the New Service Provisioning time from 2 weeks to 10 minutes, including automated CICD and monitoring setup. Talent Acquisition  Mentorship: Re-engineered the technical interviewing process, focusing on\nsystems design and behavioral competencies. Successfully hired 60 top-tier.NET engineers and\nestablished a mentorship program that resulted in a 95 engineering retention rate over 3 years. Cost Optimization: Leveraged Azure Spot Instances for non-critical processing workloads and\ntransitioned 80 of background tasks to Azure Functions (Serverless), saving the company 6.2M\nin annual cloud spend. Technical Due Diligence: Conducted architectural audits for 4 strategic acquisitions, identifying\nover 8M in technical debt and leading the integration of diverse.NET stacks into the core Nexus", "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "(AIDriven Healthtech Platform", "company_name": "(AIDriven Healthtech Platform", "role": "Lead Architect Connect Realtime Data Interoperability", "job_title": "Lead Architect Connect Realtime Data Interoperability", "location": "Austin, TX", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "M Patients", "clients": ["M Patients"], "description": ": Real-Time Telemetry Engine: Architected a high-frequency telemetry ingestion engine using Sig-\nnalR and.NET Core. Processed 2.5 billion data points daily from wearable medical devices with\nsub-100ms latency to clinician dashboards. Healthcare Compliance (HIPAA): Implemented a zero-trust data access model using mTLS and\nAzure Key Vault for encryption at rest and in transit. Successfully navigated 3 major federal audits\nwith zero citations. FHIR Interoperability: Developed a C-based FHIR (Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources)\nmiddleware that integrated 400 disparate hospital EMR systems. Became the industry bench-\nmark for healthcare data exchange in the South-Central region. Database Scalability: Directed the transition from a single Oracle instance to a sharded Post-\ngreSQL architecture using Citus. Improved data retrieval speeds for patient histories by 350\nwhile handling a 10x increase in data volume. CICD Excellence: Replaced a manual build process with fully automated YAML-based Azure De-\nvOps pipelines. Integrated SonarQube for static analysis and mandatory code coverage gates of\n85, reducing post-release defect density by 50. Cloud Strategy: Led the Lift and Reshape strategy for Lumina, moving legacy components to", "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "", "company_name": "", "role": "global load balancing and WAF pro primary technical liaison", "job_title": "global load balancing and WAF pro primary technical liaison", "location": null, "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "Azure Front Door", "clients": ["Azure Front Door"], "description": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "of Directors", "company_name": "of Directors", "role": "", "job_title": "", "location": null, "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "", "clients": [], "description": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "(Big Data Solutions for", "company_name": "(Big Data Solutions for", "role": "Primary Technical Lead For The Omnichannel Analytics Engine", "job_title": "Primary Technical Lead For The Omnichannel Analytics Engine", "location": "Dallas, TX", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "Global Retailers", "clients": ["Global Retailers"], "description": ": Inventory Forecasting Engine: Developed a multi-threaded forecasting engine in C utilizing\nTask Parallel Library (TPL) and PLINQ. Reduced processing time for national inventory resets from\n12 hours to 45 minutes. Micro-frontend Architecture: Spearheaded the transition of a massive retail dashboard to a\nmicro-frontend architecture using Blazor WebAssembly and C. Enabled autonomous deploy-\nment cycles for 6 different product teams. Messaging Reliability: Implemented RabbitMQ with Guaranteed Delivery patterns and DLQ\n(Dead Letter Queue) processing. Eliminated data loss during high-volume retail events like Black\nFriday and Cyber Monday. Cloud Migration Lead: Directed the migration of the core platform from a private data center\nto Microsoft Azure. Implemented a cloud-first disaster recovery strategy that reduced theoretical\n\nRTO from 24 hours to 15 minutes. Performance Tuning: Reduced P95 response times for analytical queries by 60 through the\nimplementation of materialized views in SQL Server and Redis-level caching for hot data. Mentorship: Formally mentored 12 junior developers, 8 of whom were promoted to Senior or", "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"company": "Software Development Agency", "company_name": "Software Development Agency", "role": "", "job_title": "", "location": "San Antonio, TX", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false, "client": "", "clients": [], "description": ": Legacy Modernization: Acted as the primary developer for the modernization of a legacy ASP.NET\nWeb Forms application to ASP.NET MVC for a Tier-1 insurance client (Fictional: Lone Star Insur-\nance). API Ecosystem: Built a suite of RESTful APIs for mobile application integration. Implemented\ncustom OAuth2 filters and response caching, resulting in a 40 improvement in mobile app re-\nsponsiveness. Unit Testing Advocate: Introduced the first automated unit testing framework (NUnit) to the\nagency. Increased test coverage across client projects from 0 to an average of 70 using Moq\nand TDD practices. Client Engagement: Led technical discovery sessions for 15 small-to-medium enterprise clients, producing detailed SRS documents and high-level architectural designs. KEY PROJECTS PORTFOLIO\nProject IronGrid: The Distributed Ledger Res