 code coverage gates of\n85, reducing post-release defect density by 50. Cloud Strategy: Led the Lift and Reshape strategy for Lumina, moving legacy components to\nAzure App Service while implementing Azure Front Door for global load balancing and WAF pro-\ntection. Executive Advising: Acted as the primary technical liaison to the Board of Directors, providing\nquarterly reports on system resilience, scalability projections, and the ROI of the 12M annual", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false}, {"job_title": "RD budget. Technical Lead  Senior Architect  Vertex Retail Analytics", "company_name": "Dallas, TX (Big Data Solutions for Global Retailers)", "description": "Role Overview: Primary technical lead for the Omni-Channel analytics engine, utilized by 15 of\nthe Fortune 50 retailers. Focused on large-scale data processing and real-time inventory forecasting\nusing the.NET stack. Key Measurable Achievements: Inventory Forecasting Engine: Developed a multi-threaded forecasting engine in\nC utilizing\nTask Parallel Library (TPL) and PLINQ. Reduced processing time for national inventory resets from\n12 hours to 45 minutes. Micro-frontend Architecture: Spearheaded the transition of a massive retail dashboard to a\nmicro-frontend architecture using Blazor WebAssembly and C. Enabled autonomous deploy-\nment cycles for 6 different product teams. Messaging Reliability: Implemented RabbitMQ with Guaranteed Delivery patterns and DLQ\n(Dead Letter Queue) processing. Eliminated data loss during high-volume retail events like\nBlack\nFriday and Cyber Monday. Cloud Migration Lead: Directed the migration of the core platform from a private data center\nto Microsoft Azure. Implemented a cloud-first disaster recovery strategy that reduced theoretical\nRTO from 24 hours to 15 minutes. Performance Tuning: Reduced P95 response times for analytical queries by 60 through the\nimplementation of materialized views in SQL Server and Redis-level caching for hot data. Mentorship: Formally mentored 12 junior developers, 8 of whom were promoted to\nSenior or", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": false}]}
